<br>
But role playing an evil character should never be a reason to be outride rude to other players. And role playing an evil race should not prevent you from grouping with anyone, even grouping with your real-life friend who happens to be a Dwarf (which our Troll and Ogre brethren may consider a snack). <br>
<br>
Here is a good example of role playing...<br>
<br>
Last night myself (the guild master) and 3 others in the group were camping in the entry room of Dalnir. After camping there for 15 minutes, a lone halfling Druid comes along, stares at us and asks if we could use a healer. <br>
<br>
&quot;Ohh lookssss.... a little man! My tummy is hungry! Midnight ssssnack!&quot;<br>
<br>
Halfling: &quot;Hehe silly lizards. I'll keep you guys alive if you promise not to eat me. Deal?&quot; <br>
<br>
&quot;Soundsss good little man, deal! But we might still snack on you afterwards *g*&quot; <br>
<br>
Halfling: &quot;LOL silly lizards&quot; <br>
<br>
And so we had the hafling fighting in our group for the next hour or so. <br>
<br>
Role playing does not have to be a rude or negative experience. Sometimes it does get out of hand and it does tick off people. You just have to know when it is appropriate and when it is not. <br>
<br>
We have a couple trolls in the guild already, and would welcome more as our &quot;Big Enforcers&quot;. Contact me (Massadar) or speak to Joad, one of my officers. <br>
